- cs.ET (Emerging Technologies): The paper proposes a new solution for realizing multi-input-bit gates in noise-based logic processors, which can be considered an emerging technology in the field of computer science.
- cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms): The paper discusses the complexity of executing and repeating operations on exponentially large superpositions, which involves algorithmic considerations.
- cs.LO (Logic in Computer Science): The paper deals with logic gates and their implementation in noise-based logic processors, which falls under the scope of this sub-category.
- cs.PL (Programming Languages): The paper may involve programming languages used for implementing the proposed solution.
- cs.CC (Computational Complexity): The paper discusses the complexity of executing and repeating operations on exponentially large superpositions, which is a topic within computational complexity theory.
